oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.globalSearch.ui.filters
Class SearchFilterItem

java.lang.Object
  oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.globalSearch.ui.filters.SearchFilterItem
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, TilePart
Direct Known Subclasses:
CategorySearchFilterItem, KeywordSearchFilterItem, SingleSelectionSearchFilterItem, TagSearchFilterItem
public abstract class SearchFilterItem
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, TilePart

An abstract class representing a filter item. A Filter Item represents a part of the "primary key" of a search. Some Search FilterItems are root level, such as Keywords and Categories, while some are part of a hierarchy within a root level Filter Item, for example a Searchable Object within a Category.

A Search Filter item generally supports a value (and display value) which may not be set, and a list of value the user can choose from to pick the value.

If a value is not set, the filter typically displays "All", and the filter will be shown at leaf level in it's hierarchy. The hierarchy of filters is dynamic, it can grow and shrink as the user makes selections.

Some filters do not support list of values, or changing such as Keywords. A user would construct a new set of filter items with a new Keyword filter to run a new Search.

A SearchFilterItem is also a TilePart so that it can be displayed in the UI flattened as a filter.

See Also:
CategorySearchFilterItem, KeywordSearchFilterItem, FacetSearchFilterItem, DateRangeSearchFilterItem, TagSearchFilterItem, Serialized Form
